N8N_BASE_URL=https://docs.n8n.io/hosting/configuration/configuration-examples/base-url/
N8N_API_KEY=https://docs.n8n.io/api/

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=https://docs.cloud.google.com/endpoints/docs/frameworks/java/creating-client-ids
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=after creating client id copy client secret 
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials

LLM_API_KEY=
Choose an LLM Provider: Select a provider based on your needs
Create an Account: Sign up on the provider's official website. You will typically need to verify your email address.
Set Up Billing (if required): Many providers require payment details, even if they offer a free tier with limited usage. This prevents abuse of their services.
Navigate to API Key Section: Find the "API Keys", "Developers", or "Settings" section in your account dashboard.
Generate a New Key: Create a new secret key. You can usually name it for better organization (e.g., "Development Testing").
Securely Save Your Key: The key is usually shown only once. Copy and store it immediately in a secure location (e.g., a password manager or environment variable). Never hardcode API keys in your source code or commit them to version control.
